  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Investigate the number theoretic properties of 2023. Specifically, determine the order of 2 modulo 2023 (the smallest positive integer $d$ such that $2^d \equiv 1 \pmod{2023}$). Additionally, examine the binary structure of multiples of 2023 to see if any $2023 \cdot n$ can be expressed as a sum of very few powers of 2 (e.g., $2^a + 2^b$ or $2^a + 2^b + 2^c$)."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Determine the minimum possible value for $k(n)$, where $k(n)$ is the number of ones in the binary representation of $2023 \cdot n$ for $n \in \mathbb{Z}^+$. Test if $k(n)=1$ is possible (this would imply $2023 \cdot n = 2^a$), if $k(n)=2$ is possible (this would imply $2023 \cdot n = 2^a + 2^b$), and if not, investigate if $k(n)=3$ or higher is the minimum."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the results from helper_1 and helper_2. Use the order of 2 modulo 2023 to rule out $k(n)=1$. Use the existence (or non-existence) of solutions to the congruence $2^a \equiv \pm 2^b \pmod{2023}$ or similar forms to determine if $k(n)=2$ is achievable. The final answer should be the smallest integer $k$ for which a multiple of 2023 has exactly $k$ ones in binary."
}
```

